anime.my_comments: Enjoyable. However, despite it being slightly unreasonable, I wish all the songs were full length rather than just a couple minutes. Also, the falling action was very lacking. Despite this, I enjoyed the ride quite a bit.

The anime's greatest strength lies not in it's explicit characters or plot, but setting. Beneath the moeblob characters and the lighthearted events lies an multitude of themes that I could probably write an essay about. It makes one think and imagine and truly comprehend that these girls live in. And even if the plot cuts corners, the characters are imperfect, the scene is so real that you can almost imagine the authors hiding an alternated, more real story behind the intentional cheerful facade. And then sometimes the anime drops the facade entirely and punches you in the face with FEELS.
